benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/catalog/plan - Retrieve plan for a given subscription and date

covered: Valid Request: Covered (TC01, TC02, TC13) with correct 200 responses and plan resolution, including date-boundary behavior.
Empty/No Data: Covered via empty database and no-match paths (TC11, partially TC03/TC04).
Query Parameters: Broad coverage of combinations and validation (TC01–TC08) and handling of unexpected extras (TC14).
Error Handling: Malformed inputs (400), not found (404), system failure (503), and data integrity conflict (409/500) covered (TC05–TC08, TC10, TC12).
Security: SQL injection and XSS input validation covered (TC17, TC18).
Performance: Response time under normal and concurrent load covered (TC15, TC16).
Regression/Compatibility: Prior fixes and legacy client behavior covered (TC19, TC20).
Pagination: Not applicable to a single-resource GET endpoint (no list response).
gaps: Caching Behavior: No tests for ETag/Last-Modified/Cache-Control or conditional GET (304 Not Modified).
Rate Limiting/Throttling: No scenarios to validate 429 Too Many Requests and Retry-After headers.
Content Negotiation/Headers: No explicit checks for Content-Type: application/json or 406 when Accept is unsupported.
Schema/Contract Validation: Tests assert “valid JSON” but don’t validate against the Plan schema (#/definitions/Plan) and required fields.
Ambiguous expectations when parameters are omitted: TC03/TC04 allow multiple outcomes (200/default/empty); behavior should be deterministic per spec.
Missing negative: Valid subscriptionId + requestedDate outside any active plan window should return a defined error (e.g., 404) or explicit default; not covered.
Input edge cases: Empty string and whitespace-only values for subscriptionId/requestedDate not tested.
Authorization depth: 403 Forbidden (authenticated but not authorized) not covered.
Produces check: No verification of response Content-Type header even though spec says application/json.
recommendations: Add caching tests: verify Cache-Control/ETag/Last-Modified presence; send If-None-Match/If-Modified-Since to assert 304 behavior and correct validators.
Add rate-limiting tests: burst requests to trigger 429 and validate Retry-After and error body.
Add header/content negotiation tests: assert Content-Type: application/json on 200; send unsupported Accept to validate 406 (or documented behavior).
Add schema validation: validate the response against the Plan JSON schema (#/definitions/Plan), including required fields and types.
Make missing-parameter behavior deterministic: align with product/spec, then update TC03/TC04 to assert one clear status code and body shape.
Add scenario: subscriptionId valid + requestedDate outside plan period for that subscription; assert expected status (e.g., 404) and error payload.
Add input edge tests: empty string, whitespace, leading/trailing spaces for both parameters; expect 400 with precise validation messages.
Add authorization depth test: authenticated user lacking required scope/role should receive 403 with appropriate error.
Add explicit header check in success scenarios: verify application/json Content-Type and character set when applicable.
